{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"SerialPort: disconnect","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort/disconnect_event","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort\"><code>SerialPort</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort/readable\"><code>readable</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort/writable\"><code>writable</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Methods</summary><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort/close\"><code>close()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort/getInfo\"><code>getInfo()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort/getSignals\"><code>getSignals()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort/open\"><code>open()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort/setSignals\"><code>setSignals()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Events</summary><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort/connect_event\"><code>connect</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><em><code>disconnect</code></em></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\"><code>EventTarget</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard secure\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Secure context:</strong> This feature is available only in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Secure_Contexts\">secure contexts</a> (HTTPS), in some or all <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">supporting browsers</a>.</p></div><div class=\"notecard experimental\" id=\"sect2\"><p><strong>Experimental:</strong> <strong>This is an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Writing_guidelines/Experimental_deprecated_obsolete#experimental\">experimental technology</a></strong><br>Check the <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">Browser compatibility table</a> carefully before using this in production.</p></div>\n<p>The <strong><code>disconnect</code></strong> event of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort\"><code>SerialPort</code></a> interface is fired when the port has disconnected from the device. This event is only fired for ports associated with removable devices such as those connected via USB.</p>\n<p>This event bubbles to the instance of <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Serial\"><code>Serial</code></a> that returned this interface.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Use the event name in methods like <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget/addEventListener\" title=\"addEventListener()\"><code>addEventListener()</code></a>, or set an event handler property.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'disconnect'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">event</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function-variable function\">ondisconnect</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">event</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"event_type","title":"Event type","isH3":false,"content":"<p>A generic <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event\"><code>Event</code></a>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"bubbling","title":"Bubbling","isH3":false,"content":"<p>This event bubbles to <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Serial\"><code>Serial</code></a>. The <code>event.target</code> property refers to the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort\"><code>SerialPort</code></a> object that bubbles up.</p>\n<p>For more information, see <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Learn/JavaScript/Building_blocks/Events#event_bubbling_and_capture\">Event bubbling and capture</a>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"notify_when_a_specific_port_disconnects","title":"Notify when a specific port disconnects","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Here the event listener is installed on a specific <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort\"><code>SerialPort</code></a> object.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>port<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'disconnect'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">event</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// notify that the port has become unavailable</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"listening_for_any_ports_that_become_unavailable","title":"Listening for any ports that become unavailable","isH3":true,"content":"<p>The <code>disconnect</code> event bubbles up to the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Serial\"><code>Serial</code></a> object where you can listen for any ports that become unavailable.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>navigator<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>serial<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'disconnect'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">event</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// notify that a port has become unavailable</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// use `event.target` to refer to the unavailable port</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://wicg.github.io/serial/#dfn-disconnect","title":"Web Serial API"},{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://wicg.github.io/serial/#dom-serialport-ondisconnect","title":"Web Serial API"}],"query":"api.SerialPort.disconnect_event"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.SerialPort.disconnect_event","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort/disconnect_event/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort/connect_event\" title=\"connect\"><code>connect</code></a> event</li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Event type","id":"event_type"},{"text":"Bubbling","id":"bubbling"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The disconnect event of the SerialPort interface is fired when the port has disconnected from the device. This event is only fired for ports associated with removable devices such as those connected via USB.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:18:40.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/serialport/disconnect_event","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/serialport/disconnect_event/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/e0e09b1df51489867f2e74c18586d168ba5e00d1","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort","title":"SerialPort"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SerialPort/disconnect_event","title":"SerialPort: disconnect"}],"pageTitle":"SerialPort: disconnect - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}